modules.description: Provides polynomial evaluation, root finding, and special function computations using floating-point and complex number types. Operates on arrays and vectors for numerical analysis tasks. Enables precise calculation of Bessel functions and solving algebraic equations in scientific computing scenarios.

The module offers statistical distribution calculations, including cumulative probabilities, inverse cumulative functions, and special mathematical operations for distributions like binomial, normal, gamma, and t-distributions. It processes integers and floats to compute probabilities, quantiles, or statistical parameters. Use cases include hypothesis testing, risk analysis, and modeling probabilistic scenarios requiring precise distributional computations.
